entries.title: What do these hardliners want? Here's what they've said
entries.description: It's a very small minority of a slim majority that's kept the House from moving forward and is on the cusp of derailing Rep. Kevin McCarthy's bid to become speaker.

entries.title: The new 'Avatar' drew me in, despite my better instincts
entries.description: In the runup to the release of "Avatar: The Way of Water," director James Cameron slapped back at critics and viewers who'd expressed doubts about the franchise's continued relevance: "The trolls will have it that nobody gives a sh*t and they can't remember the characters' names or one damn thing that happened in the movie," he barked to UK movie magazine "Empire." "Then they see the movie again and go, 'Oh, okay, excuse me, let me just shut the f**k up right now.' So I'm not worried about that."

entries.title: Apple is raising the price of iPhone battery replacements
entries.description: Apple is raising the price of battery replacements for all out-of-warranty iPhone models prior to the current iPhone 14 lineup, the company confirmed on its website.

entries.title: His team is holding discussions about adjourning the US House until tomorrow, but he may not have the votes to delay a fourth ballot
McCarthy allies want to adjourn for the day but he may not have the votes to delay a fourth ballot, sources say
Well-behaved canine bus riders go viral
entries.description: Who picks the seat when dogs in Alaska ride their very own doggie bus? CNN's Jeanne Moos explains what the "licky puppy corner" is.

entries.title: Iranian authorities release prominent actress Taraneh Alidoosti on bail
entries.description: One of Iran's best-known actresses, who was arrested after she criticized the execution of a man involved in nationwide protests, was released on bail on Wednesday, state-aligned ISNA said.

entries.title: The man trying to quietly lock down votes for McCarthy
entries.description: As House GOP leader Kevin McCarthy struggles to secure votes within his party to secure speakership of the chamber, he has tapped a longtime Republican lawmaker to quietly try and lock down votes among the GOP holdouts.

entries.title: Sharon Osbourne reveals daughter Kelly has welcomed her first child
entries.description: Sharon Osbourne revealed that her daughter Kelly Osbourne has quietly welcomed a baby, her first, with her boyfriend, Sid Wilson.

entries.title: Ukraine's defense intel chief predicts attacks 'deeper and deeper' inside Russia
Dionne Warwick says she and Dolly Parton have a gospel duet planned
entries.description: Two living legends have a special collaboration in the works.

entries.title: Driver falls 21 feet into house while fleeing police
entries.description: As New Jersey police approached a suspected stolen vehicle, the driver tried to flee but lost control of the car and drove off an embankment, falling into a house. No residents or bystanders were injured.

entries.title: Europe's recession may not be as bad as feared
entries.description: European stocks are pushing higher for the third straight day as investors cheer signs that inflation, supply chain bottlenecks and natural gas prices are all easing

entries.title: Gabrielle Union 'felt entitled' to infidelity during first marriage
entries.description: Gabrielle Union is sharing more about her first marriage that she describes as "dysfunctional from day one."

entries.title: Aldi sales soar as UK shoppers battle record food inflation
entries.description: Aldi recorded its highest-ever December sales in the United Kingdom, as shoppers squeezed by searing food price inflation flocked to the German discount supermarket chain to save money on groceries.

entries.title: Why Ocasio-Cortez was talking to congressman who once posted an anime video showing him killing her
entries.description: Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez (D-NY) and Rep. Paul Gosar (R-AZ) were seen talking during the vote for House Speaker. In November of 2021, Gosar tweeted a doctored anime video that depicted himself killing both Ocasio-Cortez and President Joe Biden.

entries.title: Star nursery revealed at the tail of the Serpens constellation
entries.description: Astronomers glimpsed a stellar nursery in a new light, thanks to the Visible and Infrared Survey Telescope for Astronomy in Chile.

entries.title: Cristiano Ronaldo 'proud' of move to Al Nassr and says his work in Europe is 'done'
entries.description: Portuguese superstar Cristiano Ronaldo was officially unveiled by his new Saudi Arabian club Al Nassr on Tuesday in Riyadh, explaining he made the move having "won everything" in Europe.

entries.title: Inflation fears fade as geopolitical risks rise
entries.description: Inflation fears roiled the markets in 2022. Now, investors may have scarier things to worry about in 2023, according to a report from global research and consulting firm Eurasia Group. Most notable? Concerns about the increasingly chaotic geopolitical landscape.

entries.title: A single Iranian attack drone found to contain parts from more than a dozen US companies
European ski resorts close due to lack of snow
entries.description: Christine Harrison has been visiting Le Praz De Lys-Sommand, a small ski resort in the French Alps, for the past 20 years. The view out of her chalet window has always been more or less the same -- wide expanse of mountains, hills and chalets, all capped in frothy, thick snow.

entries.title: Damar Hamlin's sudden collapse sent ESPN scrambling. How Scott Van Pelt shifted from covering a game to a crisis
entries.description: "Sports is important. And suddenly it's not."

entries.title: Damar Hamlin's doctors are working to get him breathing without a ventilator
entries.description: After suffering a cardiac arrest mid-game on Monday, Buffalo Bills safety Damar Hamlin remains sedated on a ventilator as doctors work toward getting him to breathe on his own, according to an update from the player's uncle.

entries.title: Lionel Messi returns to Paris Saint-Germain training after Argentina's World Cup victory
entries.description: Lionel Messi has returned to the Paris Saint-Germain training center after winning the World Cup with Argentina last month.

entries.title: Video shows moment of explosion at Russian ammo depot
entries.description: Ukraine's military has shared a video it says shows the destruction of a Russian ammunition warehouse in Svatove, a strategic hub in the eastern Luhansk region.

entries.title: What to do if someone is in cardiac arrest
entries.description: If you suspect that someone has gone into cardiac arrest, there are some simple steps you can take right away that could mean the difference between life and death.

entries.title: A single Iranian attack drone found to contain parts from more than a dozen US companies
entries.description: Parts made by more than a dozen US and Western companies were found inside a single Iranian drone downed in Ukraine last fall, according to a Ukrainian intelligence assessment obtained exclusively by CNN.

entries.title: Hakeem Jeffries to make history as the first Black lawmaker to lead a party in Congress
entries.description: Rep. Hakeem Jeffries is expected to make history as the first Black lawmaker to lead a party in Congress as the 118th Congress convenes in Washington.

entries.title: Biden heads to Kentucky to tout bipartisan infrastructure bill with Republican Sen. Mitch McConnell
entries.description: A rare scene is set to unfold in Covington, Kentucky, on Wednesday: President Joe Biden standing alongside Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell, as the two men promote together a major bipartisan legislative accomplishment.

entries.title: US-made HIMARS used in strike that killed Russian troops, Moscow says
Ash Barty to mentor wildcard Gadecki at Australian Open
entries.description: Retired Australian Open champion Ash Barty is returning to Melbourne Park for this year's event to mentor local hope Olivia Gadecki, who received a wildcard for the season's first Grand Slam.

entries.title: Poland says Germany refused talks on World War II reparations
entries.description: Germany has rebuffed the latest push by Poland's nationalist government for vast reparations over World War II, saying in response to a diplomatic note that the issue was closed, the foreign ministry in Warsaw said on Tuesday.

entries.title: Snooker investigates Chinese players over alleged match-fixing scandal
entries.description: Snooker's governing body on Tuesday said it had suspended two more Chinese players as it investigates an alleged match-fixing and betting scandal -- bringing the number of players from the Asian country caught up in the probe to 10.

entries.title: NFL star Damar Hamlin remains in critical condition

entries.description:
• Video: See aftermath of apparent Ukrainian strike on Russian army barracks
• Banksy mural theft ringleader could face 12 years in jail, Ukraine says

entries.title: From Harry Styles and Brad Pitt to Jared Leto, what's behind the A-list male beauty brand trend?
entries.description: The celebrity beauty brand train has become standing-room only, including Rihanna's Fenty, Rare Beauty from Selena Gomez, SKKN by Kim (Kardashian), and Haus Labs by Lady Gaga, to name just a few. Until recently, the majority of stars launching lines to help us glow up were women.

entries.title: Jeremy Renner thanks his fans for their sympathies in his first social media post after snow plowing accident
entries.description: Actor Jeremy Renner thanked fans from his hospital bed Tuesday as he continued to recover from two surgeries following being injured by a snowplow machine in what officials described as "a tragic accident."

entries.title: US Soccer announces investigation into men's head coach Gregg Berhalter as he releases statement on 1991 domestic violence incident
entries.description: US Soccer has launched an investigation into men's national team head coach Gregg Berhalter, the organization announced Tuesday, as the coach released a statement addressing a previous domestic violence incident between himself and his-now wife.

entries.title: Nuclear weapons expert demonstrates impact a 'dirty bomb' can have
entries.description: Russia is accusing Ukraine of planning to use a so-called "dirty bomb", an allegation dismissed by Kyiv and its Western allies as a false-flag operation that Moscow could use as a pretext to escalate the Kremlin's war against its neighbor. CNN's Clare Sebastian reports.

entries.title: Tokyo is so crowded the government is paying families to leave
entries.description: Japan is offering to pay families to move out of its overcrowded capital, in an effort to revitalize countryside towns and boost the falling birth rate.

entries.title: Indians demand justice for Delhi woman dragged to her death
entries.description: Angry crowds gathered in Delhi on Tuesday, demanding justice for a scooter rider who was killed and dragged by a car for miles through the streets of India's capital.

entries.title: US-made rocket launchers used in strike that killed Russian troops, Moscow says
Delta jet runs off the end of a taxiway amid icy conditions at Minnesota airport
entries.description: A Delta jet slid off the end of a taxiway at Minneapolis-St. Paul International Airport amid icy conditions Tuesday night, officials said.

entries.title: 'I thought I would die on that boat': Mother recalls the horror of month at sea
entries.description: Hatemon Nesa weeps as she clings to her 5-year-old daughter, Umme Salima, at a rescue shelter in Indonesia's Aceh province. Their faces appear gaunt, their eyes sullen, after drifting for weeks at sea on a boat with little food or water.

entries.title: Pakistan to shut markets and restaurants early to save power amid economic crisis
entries.description: Pakistan's economic woes show no signs of letting up in 2023.

entries.title: After a revolt of ultra-hardliners dashed McCarthy's bid to become speaker, Republicans are unable to assume the control they won in the midterms
entries.description: Governing by chaos is back.

entries.title: What happens in the House when there is no speaker? Not a lot
entries.description: House Republicans' failure to elect a speaker on Tuesday after multiple rounds of voting isn't just denying the GOP a leader -- it's holding up much of the functioning of the chamber.

entries.title: Videos show both sides of US-China aerial encounter -- and highlight the risks involved
entries.description: The interception of a United States Air Force reconnaissance jet by a Chinese fighter over the South China Sea last month should be seen as a potential warning of how easily, and quickly things can go terribly wrong -- raising the risk of a deadly military confrontation between the two powers, analysts say.

entries.title: Australia cruise ship stopped for biofuel cleaning will compensate passengers
entries.description: Viking Cruises will compensate hundreds of passengers on its Orion cruise ship after cruisers were forced to stay on board and miss multiple stops because officials blocked port access due to marine growth on the ship's hull.

entries.title: Missouri carries out first known execution of an openly transgender person for 2003 murder
entries.description: Missouri carried out the first known US execution of an openly transgender person Tuesday when Amber McLaughlin, who was convicted of a 2003 murder and unsuccessfully sought clemency from the governor, was put to death by lethal injection.

entries.title: Thousands bid farewell as Pelé is laid to rest
entries.description: Thousands lined the streets of Santos, Brazil, to view the funeral procession of soccer icon Pelé. CNN's Stefano Pozzebon reports.

entries.title: Hear what McCarthy told CNN about the possibility of dropping out
entries.description: Rep. Kevin McCarthy (R-CA) spoke with reporters hours after he lost three rounds of voting for the role of Speaker of the House.

entries.title: China's new supercarrier will soon undergo first sea trials, officer says
entries.description: The Chinese navy's massive new aircraft carrier, the CNS Fujian, is expected to head to sea for the first time this year, the ship's executive officer said in an interview with state media.

entries.title: Hear what Idaho murder suspect did during extradition hearing
entries.description: CNN's Jean Casarez reports on what happened inside a Pennsylvania courtroom where Brian Kohberger, the suspect in the November slaying of four University of Idaho students, waived extradition from his home state of Pennsylvania to face murder charges in the state of Idaho.

entries.title: Teammate describes watching Damar Hamlin collapse
entries.description: Buffalo Bills offensive tackle Dion Dawkins talks to CNN's Wolf Blitzer about watching teammate Damar Hamlin collapse and be revived on the field during a Monday Night Football game against the Cincinnati Bengals.

entries.title: NYC mayor, a vocal rat opponent, faces more fines for rat infestation at Brooklyn property
entries.description: New York Mayor Eric Adams was hit with new fines over a rat infestation at one of his properties in Brooklyn, just one day after a different rodent infestation ticket at the same property was dismissed.

entries.title: Video: Hamlin's uncle describes moment family saw him collapse onto the field
entries.description: CNN's Adrienne Broaddus talks to Damar Hamlin's uncle Dorrian Glenn about the moment he saw his nephew collapse during a game against the Cincinnati Bengals.
